annotation.TEXT: It looks impossible to get through unhurt, but there's gotta be a way...

1 vote for Mario to use his cape to dive bomb the YouTube staff, 3 votes to feed YouTube's staff to silver munchers, 1 vote for Mario to eat Yuyuko and Kirby pasta (Ick!), 1 vote for Bowser to tie up Mother Brain and force her to watch the entire saga of a vampire movie which will remain nameless, and may or may not include werewolves, 1 vote for an end to the silly votes, 1 vote for me to go to space, 1 vote for me to do voice commentary (Sorry, but that's beyond my capability right now.), 1 vote for me to make Conway's Game of Life in SMW, 1 vote for Super Mario 3D Land's 8-Crown (I think I overlooked this vote in a previous episode somehow.), 1 vote for Star-3-1, 6 votes for the world 7 fortress, and 8 votes for secret world 2! Okay!
30 seconds left, and I'm at Yoshi coin #4...
There's the goal, but where's the last Yoshi coin? Well, judging by the wall spring up here...
Only 29? Bah...
Okay, so we've got some layer 2 foliage that blocks some of view. Also, what's this music? Anybody know? UPDATE: It's "Haunted Forest" from an SNES game called "Whirlo". Thanks, zigil1!
Uh, oh. Silver munchers. Make sure not to get near them if possible!
Aha! I did need the platform!
Alright, now I could continue with the secret world, but I think that fortress has been waiting long enough, and it did get a decent number of votes, so I'm doing it next!
Apparently a waterfall cave is a good place to hold a disco party, and it's pretty safe too, as long as the blue switch is active!
Yoink!
Nothing up here...
Whoa! Fragile floor! At least there's some perfectly solid spots.
That's all the Yoshi coins, and I guess it's boss time!
There was another obscured Yoshi coin there.
And now we've got saws being thrown into the mix.
Oh, that's a low time limit. Better not loiter around anywhere more than necessary.
...And so is this castle.
Well, this level's done, and didn't take very long. Now it's bonus game time again!
Alright, now as I was saying, there's enough time for one more level, so... let's do another secret world level!
Yay. Another mushroom that I don't need.
Hey, it's time for more Super SIG World 21! Now, let's take a look at those voting results:
I hope I'll do alright without the cape.
Doesn't look like it... And, I think I'm being attacked by a hidden Lakitu up there. Better finish the level now.
Conveyor belts are here too, it seems.
Close call there. Also, thank you blue switch blocks!
Uh, is it normal to be practicing punting in a waterfall cave?
No? I thought for sure that brick would've held a coin or something... I hope I didn't just screw myself! Well, I can keep going to the right...
Luckily, I can get a replacement feather right here. Now, let's try not to get burned anymore!
More blue koopas. It's like the game wants me to break some of these levels with Yoshi!
Now for the last one...
Okay, got them all, and I'm near the goal, so I might as well...
Spikes are no match for Yoshi's shoes!
Also, I'll want to search for hidden items. You never know when you'll find a Yoshi coin that's obscured behind this green stuff.
And now I'm back here. Okay, so that room serves to reset those bricks in case I broke the one under the door, and power me up in case I was small. Also, a Yoshi coin for 100% completionists.
Also, podoboos, which catch an all-too-eager Mario off-guard.
I must've missed that Yoshi coin somewhere during the main part of the level. Of course, I'm going to give the level another sweep in search of it.
Now, as I was saying, I might as well just complete the level again since I'm right near the goal.
Oho! There was a Yoshi coin up there!
To be continued...
Ack! My head!

Even the purple buzzies want to join in on the fun! Also, I've already gotten three Yoshi coins, so I gotta be about halfway done. Given my remaining time, I'm more convinced now that that platform will be needed eventually.
Easy enough from that solid spot.
And we open with a Roto-Disc and an all-too-eager Maverick Thwomp.
I'd better make sure I don't get too far ahead of that platform.
Umm... How do I get past them?
This section would be much trickier without Yoshi! (Well, maybe not "much"...)
Heh. I ate a football out of nowhere there! I've gotta be careful for hidden threats here.
Found it! It was hidden up top just after those red buzzies.
D'oh.
Okay, so secret level 4 is open now...
I should wipe out that Lava Lotus before it can shoot more fireballs if I can.
Yeah, I'll take another feather.
I'm going to make use of a blue koopa this time!
This reminds me of those rooms in SMB3's Bowser's castle that you end up in if you take the wrong door, which send you back to the start.
Die Ninjis! You don't belong in this world! (Oh, wait. It's Dracula that doesn't belong in this world. Sorry, Ninjis!)
That opens up the regular castle, which I'm not going to do now. However, I think there's enough time for one more level, but first...
Hmm... Door on a brick... Well, then obviously...
Also, another feather. Cool.
So, which level should I play next? Secret-4 or 7-Castle? Vote now, and we'll find out next time!
Well, that didn't work. I wonder how you're supposed to get through them unscathed...
There's a flower in this block here, but I'm going to stick with my two feathers.
Oh, I see a Yoshi coin on the lower path, so of course I'm going back for it!
This one has a Yoshi coin at least, though.
...MOOOOOONNNNNN!!!!!! There was a moon hidden offscreen here!
Gah! I hit the upper block at a bad angle and it threw off my movement there.
Hmm... There was a gap in the coins there, I think, but I couldn't find anything above it.
I'm sure it's not normal to be practicing pitching in a waterfall cave. Also, lag and apparently the sprite limit make this part easier than expected.
No Yoshi because he forgot his passport.
Is the last Yoshi coin on the other side of this pipe?
Good thing I did. This part looks tricky enough without fireballs cluttering up the place!
Okay, we've got some nice DKC water level music, a mushroom that I don't need, and a platform rising through a layer 2 waterfall that I probably will need, knowing this game.
